##PROJECT REPORT - Expense Tracker using Python

##1. Introduction
Managing daily expenses is an important skill for students, especially those living in hostels. Many students tend to overspend because they do not keep track of their daily expenses. This project aims to provide a simple and efficient solution to track and manage expenses using Python.

##2. Problem Statement
Students often face difficulty in managing their finances due to lack of proper tracking. Without monitoring expenses, it becomes hard to control spending and maintain a budget.

##3. Objective
The main objectives of this project are:
To develop a simple expense tracking system
To help users record and monitor daily expenses
To calculate total spending
To identify the highest expense
To store data permanently using file handling

##4. Methodology
The project is implemented using the Python programming language. The following concepts are used:
Lists to store expense data
Dictionaries to store amount and category
Functions for modular programming
Loops for continuous execution
Conditional statements for decision making
File handling (JSON) to save and load data




##Working:
The program displays a menu with options.
The user selects an option (add/view/total/highest).
Data is stored in a list.
Expenses are saved in a file (expenses.json).
When the program restarts, saved data is loaded.

##5. Features of the Project
Add new expenses with category
View all recorded expenses
Calculate total spending
Display highest expense
Data persistence using JSON file
User-friendly menu system

##6. Tools and Technologies Used
Programming Language: Python
Editor: VS Code / IDLE
Data Storage: JSON file
Platform: GitHub

